windows
 pip install virtualenv(pip used install third party software)
activate
<myenv>/scripts/activate
linux
 sudo apt-get install python3-pip

upgrade pip:
python -m pip install --upgrade pip

create virtualenv
virtualenv <project/envornment name>

how to activate virtualenv
source myenv/bin/activate

deactivate the virtualenv
deactivate

if python 2 version then  python 3.2.5
virtualenv -p python3 <envname>myenv

to install django
pip install django==1.11.13(these is lts version of jgango)

to check django install or not
django-admin --version

it show all s/w in virtual env
pip list --local

django -admin startproject <projectname>

to run your project
python manage.py runserver

process :
step1 :external mywebsite ->views: define the function

step2: external mywebsite-> urls: define the url on particular task perform

step3 : access

 mange.py : parent main project-> settings.py(main prg)-> urls(mainprg)

to create app
python manage.py startapp appname


